text: The 3-in-1 ($1.40) was crispy and served hot, which was nice. However, I find the taste flat. Also, even though it's called "3 in 1", I could only taste yam and Nian Gao. Where is the third ingredient haha.

This stall sells nostalgic old-school snacks that really hit the spot. The carrot cake sticks are especially good—the more you munch on them, the more flavorful they get. You know what I mean, right? That kind of satisfying, addictive taste that keeps you going back for more. I also really enjoyed their Tau Suan and Tau Huay—simple, comforting, and well-made. It’s so heartening to see these kinds of traditional stalls still thriving in Singapore.

Warm Tau Suan ( Mung Bean Soup ) with Curry Potato Puff, a good meatless breakfast.
Great for everyone, vegetarians and non-vegetarians.
Tau Suan was only average, but their carrot cake sticks were super hot and crispy!
